cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Computational Pathology Research Repository: Multimodal Fusion with Temporal Reasoning"
abstract: "A research repository implementing novel multimodal fusion architectures for computational pathology. Combines whole-slide images (WSI), genomic features, and clinical text through attention-based fusion, incorporates cross-slide temporal reasoning for disease progression analysis, implements transformer-based stain normalization, and provides self-supervised pretraining objectives tailored to histopathology data."
authors:
  - family-names: "Research"
    given-names: "Computational Pathology"
repository-code: "https://github.com/your-username/computational-pathology-research"
keywords:
  - computational pathology
  - multimodal fusion
  - deep learning
  - whole-slide imaging
  - temporal reasoning
  - stain normalization
  - self-supervised learning
  - attention mechanisms
license: MIT
